"{\"uid\": \"tribune.com.pk-story-2495040-former-boyfriend-of-ugandan-olympic-athlete-rebecca-cheptegei-who-set-her-on-fire-has-died\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"US  Ex-boyfriend of Ugandan Olympian Rebecca Cheptegei, responsible for setting her on fire, has passed away  The former boyfriend of Ugandan Olympic athlete Rebecca Cheptegei, who set her on fire in a deadly attack, has died from burns sustained during the incident.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 2, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9958123761272961, \"rank\": 0.004025463309628419, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 0.9999999998212843, \"rank\": 1.7718134083681936e-10, \"text\": \"Ugandan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}, {\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 44, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"score\": 0.8284880773894491, \"rank\": 0.20701604951068697, \"text\": \"Rebecca\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\"}, {\"begin\": 134, \"end\": 141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 0.9999999998212843, \"rank\": 1.7718134083681936e-10, \"text\": \"Ugandan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}, {\"begin\": 158, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"score\": 0.8284880773894491, \"rank\": 0.20701604951068697, \"text\": \"Rebecca\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dickson Ndiema, who ambushed Cheptegei as she returned home from church, doused her with petrol and set her ablaze in Trans Nzoia County, Kenya.\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 268, \"end\": 275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Steel_Dickson\", \"score\": 0.5100414106083865, \"rank\": 0.5236322241134911, \"text\": \"Dickson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Steel_Dickson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Steel_Dickson\"}, {\"begin\": 406, \"end\": 411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 8.823687805744752e-14, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Local authorities reported that the two had been in conflict over a small piece of land.\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ndiema died in the intensive care unit at Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital, where he had been admitted with over 30% burns.\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 627, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cheptegei, 33, died from 80% burns four days after the attack.\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Neighbours recalled hearing screams as the athlete ran toward them seeking help.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr. Owen Menach from Moi Hospital confirmed Ndiema's death, stating, \\\"It's true he has died from the burn injuries.\\\"\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menach\", \"score\": 0.9999999734066026, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Menach\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menach\"}, {\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_arap_Moi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.781157991737021e-21, \"text\": \"Moi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_arap_Moi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_arap_Moi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The attack has shocked many, with Cheptegei being the third female athlete killed by an intimate partner in Kenya in recent years.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 999, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 8.823687805744752e-14, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, world-record holder Agnes Tirop was fatally stabbed, and six months later, athlete Damaris Mutua was strangled.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1051, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agnes_Tirop\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agnes Tirop\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agnes_Tirop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agnes_Tirop\"}, {\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damaris_(biblical_figure)\", \"score\": 0.9999999689825931, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Damaris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damaris_(biblical_figure)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damaris_(biblical_figure)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cheptegei, who represented Uganda in the Paris Olympics, was described as a \\\"champion\\\" by those in her home region.\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.91911172279904e-15, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She will be buried at her ancestral home in Bukwo, Uganda.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\", \"score\": 0.9990832851328519, \"rank\": 0.0009175560043704597, \"text\": \"Bukwo\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.91911172279904e-15, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"COMMENTS  Comments are moderated and generally will be posted if they are on-topic and not abusive.\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more information, please see ourComments FAQ  This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten,                     redistributed or derived from.\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unless otherwise stated, all content is                     copyrighted \\u00a9 2025 The Express Tribune.\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": []}]}"